  "color_desc": {
    "kicker": "The color · in plain words",
    "title_html": "What you're <em>looking</em> at.",
    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "The most common asphalt-shingle install nationally is a gray in this exact tonal zone. Natural Wood sits right inside that fairway: dark enough to feel anchored, light enough to keep the elevation breathing. The granule blend is engineered to read as a single quiet plane from the street.",
      "The shingle profile carries a deep shadow line that emphasizes the gray tone in midday light. At dusk the whole roof becomes one quiet plane that frames the rest of the house instead of competing with it.",
      "Pairs cleanly with white, cream, navy, sage, and warm terra-cotta sidings. Almost any house color works underneath it."
    ],
